cs.LG, cs.DM, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.NE 

The paper deals with feature selection in a multi-class classification problem using a multi-objective evolutionary algorithm. This falls under the category of machine learning and data mining, which is covered by cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.DM (Data Mining). The paper also mentions the use of naive Bayes, which is a popular algorithm in the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of big data is also emphasized, which falls under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the use of evolutionary algorithms for optimization is a common technique in the field of neural networks (cs.NE).
